  "text": "The ConfigMap and Secret immutability feature in kubernetes/kubernetes is implemented across three main components:\n\n**1. API Type Definitions:**\nThe Immutable field is defined as a pointer to bool (*bool) in both the versioned API types (staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go) and internal API types (pkg/apis/core/types.go). For Secret, it's defined at line 7902 in v1/types.go and line 6570 in internal types.go. For ConfigMap, it's defined at line 8045 in v1/types.go and line 6698 in internal types.go. The field being optional nil allows distinguishing between explicitly set values and unset values.\n\n**2. Mutation Prevention Logic:**\nThe validation logic is implemented in pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go. The ValidateSecretUpdate function (line 7756) checks if the old Secret is immutable (line 7760). If it is, it validates that:\n- The immutable field itself cannot be reverted or changed to false (line 7761-7762)\n- The data field cannot be modified (line 7764-7765)\n\nIdentically, ValidateConfigMapUpdate (line 7813) performs the same checks for ConfigMap's data and binaryData fields (lines 7821-7825). These validation functions are called through the registry strategy layer (pkg/registry/core/secret/strategy.go and pkg/registry/core/configmap/strategy.go) in their ValidateUpdate methods (lines 89 and 87 respectively).\n\n**3. Watch Optimization for Immutable Objects:**\nThe watch optimization that skips immutable objects is implemented in the kubelet managers. The pkg/kubelet/util/manager/watch_based_manager.go contains the core logic:\n- It defines an isImmutableFunc type (line 45) that takes a runtime.Object and returns bool\n- The objectCacheItem struct has an immutable field (line 65) and a setImmutable method (line 93)\n- When an object is retrieved via GetObject, if it is immutable (checked at line 349 using c.isImmutable(object)), the reflector watch is stopped via item.setImmutable() and item.stop() (lines 350-351)\n- This prevents unnecessary watch events for objects that will never change\n\nThe isImmutable callbacks are initialized in:\n- pkg/kubelet/secret/secret_manager.go (line 150-155): checks if secret.Immutable != nil && *secret.Immutable\n- pkg/kubelet/configmap/configmap_manager.go (line 149-154): checks if configMap.Immutable != nil && *configMap.Immutable\n\nBoth callbacks are passed to NewWatchBasedManager (defined at line 395 in watch_based_manager.go), which creates an objectCache with these callbacks and passes them to NewObjectCache (line 412).\n\nThe test coverage is found in pkg/apis/core/validation/validation_test.go, with TestValidateSecretUpdate (line 22337) and TestValidateConfigMapUpdate (line 23624) verifying that immutable objects cannot have their data modified, the immutable flag cannot be reverted, and immutable objects can still be updated if marked as immutable (e.g., no data changes)."
}

